TY  - JOUR
AU  - von Thadden, Ernst-Ludwig
T1  - Long-Term Contracts, Short-Term Investment and Monitoring
PY  - 1995
Y1  - 1995/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2298077
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 62
IS  - 4
SP  - 557
EP  - 575
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - The paper presents a dynamic contracting model of myopic firm behaviour caused by the fear of early project termination by outside investors. Although the parties can conclude longterm contracts, asymmetric information between investors and firms can make it impossible to implement profitable long-term projects. The paper characterizes the structure of optimal, renegotiation-proof contracts for unmonitored and monitored finance. Monitoring by investors, although itself subject to distorting incentive constraints, is shown to be able to overcome the short-term bias of investment and thus to lengthen the firms' planning horizon.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2298077
ER  - 



